// This is optional — if there's no ambiguity, explicit import is not needed
// # std/math

// Both calling styles are valid:
// 1. Direct function style (always works, builtin):
b = sin(1.0)

// 2. Module.function style (works even without explicit # std/math):
a = math.sin(1.0)

// Both produce identical LLVM IR
print('a:', a)
print('b:', b)